                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4719.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-26T12:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1912—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mexican Government is most vague and unsatisfactory with reference to conditions
                    in Sonora. I doubt its ability to dominate situation in Sonora. I shall,
                    however, make renewed efforts to-day. Capt. Burnside greatly doubts ability of
                    the Mexican Government to send a force of any degree of efficiency except from
                    the immediate command of Gen. Huerta in Chihuahua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
